      "question": "A vertical pole of length $6$ $m$ casts a shadow $4$ $m$ long on the ground and at the same time a tower casts a shadow $28$ $m$ long. Find the height of the tower.",
      "answer": "$42$ $m$",
      "solution": {
        "steps": [
          "Recognize that the triangles formed by the objects and their shadows are similar due to the same sun angle.",
          "Set up the proportion $\\frac{Height_1}{Shadow_1} = \\frac{Height_2}{Shadow_2}$ and solve for the tower height."
        ],
        "derivation": "$\\frac{6}{4} = \\frac{h}{28} \\Rightarrow 4h = 168 \\Rightarrow h = 42$ $m$"
